    "response": "I see there are still some problematic values. Let me analyze the data more carefully and refine the conversion logic to handle more edge cases:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"analysis\": \"The output file is correctly formatted with 2548 rows and 63 columns. However, I notice several issues:\\n\\n1. Serum_Creatinine of 731.00 (patient 2590) - this is clearly in \u00b5mol/L and should be converted\\n2. BUN values like 177.24, 188.40, 191.14 are outside normal range (7-20 mg/dL) - might be in mmol/L\\n3. Hemoglobin values like 64.04, 1.90 are extreme - some might be in g/L instead of g/dL\\n4. Aluminum values like 199.80, 197.70 are very high - might need conversion\\n\\nI need to refine the conversion logic to:\\n- Handle more aggressive unit detection\\n- Apply conversions to values that are clearly in wrong units\\n- Use multiple conversion attempts for values far outside ranges\",\n  \"plan\": \"Create an improved harmonization script that:\\n1. Applies more aggressive unit detection and conversion\\n2. For each feature, tries all possible unit conversions if value is outside range\\n3. Selects the conversion that brings value closest to physiological range\\n4. Handles special cases like BUN in mmol/L, Hemoglobin in g/L, etc.\\n5. Re-validates all conversions\",\n  \"commands\": [\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"cat > /tmp/harmonize_improved.py << 'EOFIMPROVED'\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport re\\n\\n# Load data\\nprint(\\\"Loading data...\\\")\\ndf = pd.read_csv('/root/environment/data/ckd_lab_data.csv')\\n\\nprint(f\\\"Initial shape: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\\n# Step 1: Remove rows with any missing values\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nStep 1: Removing incomplete records...\\\")\\ndf_before = len(df)\\ndf = df.dropna()\\ndf_after = len(df)\\nprint(f\\\"Rows removed: {df_before - df_after}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Remaining rows: {df_after}\\\")\\n\\n# Define physiological ranges for each feature (US conventional units)\\nphysiological_ranges = {\\n    'Serum_Cre