    "response": "I see the issue - the values are still problematic. The data has many values that are clearly in wrong units but my conversion logic isn't catching them because I'm being too conservative. Let me analyze the actual data to understand the unit patterns better:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"analysis\": \"Looking at the sample output, I can see:\\n\\n1. Serum_Creatinine: values like 7.62, 19.02, 14.69 are way too high for mg/dL (normal is 0.6-1.3). These are likely in \u00b5mol/L and should be divided by 88.4\\n2. BUN: values like 74.17, 83.10, 177.24 are too high for mg/dL (normal is 7-20). These might be in mmol/L\\n3. Hemoglobin: values like 64.04, 1.90 are extreme - likely in g/L (should be 10x smaller)\\n\\nThe problem is that the raw data contains MANY values in alternative units, not just occasional outliers. I need to analyze the distribution and use a smarter detection method - if MOST values for a feature are outside the range, the data is probably in a different unit entirely.\",\n  \"plan\": \"1. Analyze the raw data to understand which features have values predominantly in alternative units\\n2. Check the distribution of values for each feature\\n3. Identify features where most values are outside the physiological range\\n4. For those features, apply a blanket conversion to the most likely alternative unit\\n5. Then apply targeted conversions for remaining outliers\",\n  \"commands\": [\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"python3 << 'EOFANALYSIS'\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport numpy as np\\n\\n# Load raw data\\ndf = pd.read_csv('/root/environment/data/ckd_lab_data.csv')\\ndf = df.dropna()\\n\\nprint(\\\"Analyzing raw data distributions...\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n# Define physiological ranges\\nphysiological_ranges = {\\n    'Serum_Creatinine': (0.6, 1.3),\\n    'BUN': (7, 20),\\n    'Hemoglobin': (12.0, 17.0),\\n    'Magnesium': (1.7, 2.2),\\n    'Serum_Calcium': (8.5, 10.2),\\n    'Ferritin': (24, 336),\\n    'Albumin_Serum': (3.5, 5.0),\\n    'Total_Protein': (6.0, 8.3),\\n}\\n\\ndef clean_value(val):\\n    if pd.isna(val) or val == '':\\n        return np.nan\\n    val_str = str(val).strip().replace(',', '.')\\n    try:\\n        return float(val_str)\\n    except ValueError:\\n        return np.nan\\n\\nfor feature in physiological_ranges.keys():\\n    if feature not in df.columns:\\n        continue\\n    \\n    # Clean values\\n    values = df[feature].apply(clean_value)\\n    values = values.dropna()\\n    \\n    min_range, max_range = physiological_ranges[feature]\\n    in_range = ((values >= min_range) & (values <= max_range)).sum()\\n    total = len(values)\\n    pct_in_range = (in_range / total * 100) if total > 0 else 0\\n    \\n    print(f\\\"{feature}:\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"  Range: {min_range} - {max_range}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"  Values in range: {in_range}/{total} ({pct_in_range:.1f}%)\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"  Min: {values.min():.2f}, Max: {values.max():.2f}, Median: {values.median():.2f}\\\")\\n    print()\\n\\nEOFANALYSIS\\n\",\n      \"duration\": 2.0\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"
