    "response": "Good progress! The conversions are being applied, but I see some values are still problematic (e.g., Serum_Calcium of 0.54, 1.20 are too low; some BUN values are still too high). Let me refine the logic further to handle the mixed-unit cases better:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"analysis\": \"The blanket conversions are working better, but there are still issues:\\n\\n1. **Serum_Calcium**: Values like 0.54, 1.20, 0.97 are too low (normal 8.5-10.2). Some values might already be in mg/dL and shouldn't be converted.\\n2. **BUN**: Values like 26.49, 29.68, 63.30, 47.73, 46.93, 67.29, 46.96, 68.26 are still outside range (7-20). Need better detection.\\n3. **Magnesium**: Some values like 0.81, 1.20, 1.35 are borderline low.\\n\\nThe issue is that not ALL values in these features are in alternative units - some are already in the correct units. I need a smarter approach that:\\n1. Checks if a value is already in range\\n2. Only converts values that are clearly outside the range\\n3. For each value, tries conversions and picks the one that brings it closest to the physiological range\",\n  \"plan\": \"Implement a hybrid approach:\\n1. For each value, first check if it's already in physiological range\\n2. If not, try available conversions\\n3. Select the conversion that brings the value closest to the center of the physiological range\\n4. This way, mixed-unit data will be handled correctly\"\n}\n```\n\nLet me create a more sophisticated conversion strategy:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"commands\": [\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"cat > /tmp/harmonize_hybrid.py << 'EOFHYBRID'\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport numpy as np\\n\\nprint(\\\"Loading data...\\\")\\ndf = pd.read_csv('/root/environment/data/ckd_lab_data.csv')\\nprint(f\\\"Initial shape: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nStep 1: Removing incomplete records...\\\")\\ndf_before = len(df)\\ndf = df.dropna()\\ndf_after = len(df)\\nprint(f\\\"Rows removed: {df_before - df_after}, Remaining: {df_after}\\\")\\n\\n# Physiological ranges\\nphysiological_ranges = {\\n    'Serum_Creatinine': (0.6, 1.3),\\n    'BUN': (7, 20),\\n    'eGFR': (0, 150),\\n    'Cystatin_C': (0.5, 1.0),\\n    'BUN_Creatinine_Ratio': (10, 20),\\n    'Sodium': (136, 145),\\n    'Potassium': (3.5, 5.0),\\n    'Chloride': (98, 107),\\n    'Bicarbonate': (23, 29),\\n    'Anion_Gap': (8, 16),\\n    'Magnesium': (1.7, 2.2),\\n    'Serum_Calcium': (8.5, 10.2),\\n    'Ionized_Calcium': (4.5, 5.3),\\n    'Phosphorus': (2.5, 4.5),\\n    'Intact_PTH': (10, 65),\\n    'Vitamin_D_25OH': (20, 100),\\n    'Vitamin_D_1_25OH': (20, 76),\\n    'Alkaline_Phosphatase': (30, 120),\\n    'Hemoglobin': (12.0, 17.0),\\n    'Hematocrit': (36, 46),\\n    'RBC_Count': (4.5, 5.9),\\n    'WBC_Count': (4.5, 11.0),\\n    'Platelet_Count': (150, 400),\\n    'Serum_Iron': (60, 170),\\n    'TIBC': (250, 425),\\n    'Transferrin_Saturation': (20, 50),\\n    'Ferritin': (24, 336),\\n    'Reticulocyte_Count': (0.5, 2.5),\\n    'Total_Bilirubin': (0.1, 1.2),\\n    'Direct_Bilirubin': (0.0, 0.3),\\n    'Albumin_Serum': (3.5, 5.0),\\n    'Total_Protein': (6.0, 8.3),\\n    'Prealbumin': (20, 40),\\n    'CRP': (0.0, 10.0),\\n    'Total_Cholesterol': (0, 200),\\n    'LDL_Cholesterol': (0, 130),\\n    'HDL_Cholesterol': (40, 100),\\n    'Triglycerides': (0, 150),\\n    'Non_HDL_Cholesterol': (0, 160),\\n    'Glucose': (70, 100),\\n    'HbA1c': (4.0, 6.0),\\n    'Fructosamine': (190, 320),\\n    'Uric_Acid': (3.5, 7.2),\\n    'Urine_Albumin': (0, 30),\\n    'Urine_Creatinine': (20, 300),\\n    'Albumin_to_Creatinine_Ratio_Urine': (0, 30),\\n    'Protein_to_Creatinine_Ratio_Urine': (0, 150),\\n    'Urine_Protein': (0, 150),\\n    'Urine_pH': (4.5, 8.0),\\n    'Urine_Specific_Gravity': (1.005, 1.030),\\n    'BNP': (0, 100),\\n    'NT_proBNP': (0, 125),\\n    'Troponin_I': (0, 0.04),\\n    'Troponin_T': (0, 0.04),\\n    'Free_T4': (0.8, 1.8),\\n    'Free_T3': (2.3, 4.2),\\n    'pH_Arterial': (7.35, 7.45),\\n    'pCO2_Arterial': (35, 45),\\n    'pO2_Arterial': (80, 100),\\n    'Lactate': (0.5, 2.0),\\n    'Beta2_Microglobulin': (0.7, 3.4),\\n    'Aluminum': (0, 10),\\n}\\n\\n# Conversion options for each feature\\nconversion_options = {\\n    'Serum_Creatinine': [1.0, 1/88.4],  # mg/dL or from \u00b5mol/L\\n    'BUN': [1.0, 1/2.8],  # mg/dL or from mmol/L\\n    'Magnesium': [1.0, 1/2.43, 1/1.22],  # mg/dL, from mmol/L, from mEq/L\\n    'Serum_Calcium': [1.0, 1/4.008],  # mg/dL or from mmol/L\\n    'Hemoglobin': [1.0, 0.1],  # g/dL or from g/L\\n    'Albumin_Serum': [1.0, 0.1],  # g/dL or from g/L\\n    'Total_Protein': [1.0, 0.1],  # g/dL or from g/L\\n    'Ferritin': [1.0],  # ng/mL (no conversion needed usually)\\n}\\n\\ndef clean_value(val):\\n    if pd.isna(val) or val == '':\\n        return np.nan\\n    val_str = str(val).strip().replace(',', '.')\\n    try:\\n        return float(val_str)\\n    except ValueError:\\n        return np.nan\\n\\ndef convert_value(feature, value):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Apply best conversion to bring value into physiological range\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if pd.isna(value) or feature not in physiological_ranges:\\n        return value\\n    \\n    min_range, max_range = physiological_ranges[feature]\\n    range_center = (min_range + max_range) / 2.0\\n    \\n    # If already in range, return as-is\\n    if min_range <= value <= max_range:\\n        return value\\n    \\n    # Try available conversions\\n    if feature in conversion_options:\\n        best_value = value\\n        best_distance = float('inf')\\n        \\n        for factor in conversion_options[feature]:\\n            converted = value * factor\\n            distance = abs(converted - range_center)\\n            \\n            # Prefer conversions that put value in range\\n            if min_range <= converted <= max_range:\\n                if distance < best_distance:\\n                    best_value = converted\\n                    best_distance = distance\\n            # Otherwise, track closest conversion\\n            elif best_distance == float('inf'):\\n                if distance < best_distance:\\n                    best_value = converted\\n                    best_distance = distance\\n        \\n        return best_value\\n    \\n    return value\\n\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nStep 2: Cleaning and converting values...\\\")\\nnumeric_cols = [col for col in df.columns if col != 'patient_id']\\n\\nfor col in numeric_cols:\\n    df[col] = df[col].apply(clean_value)\\n    df[col] = df[col].apply(lambda x: convert_value(col, x))\\n    df[col] = df[col].round(2)\\n\\nprint(f\\\"Cleaned {len(numeric_cols)} numeric columns\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nStep 3: Formatting values to X.XX format...\\\")\\nfor col in numeric_cols:\\n    df[col] = df[col].apply(lambda x: f\\\"{x:.2f}\\\" if pd.notna(x) else \\\"\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"\\\\nStep 4: Saving harmonized data...\\\")\\ndf.to_csv('/root/ckd_lab_data_harmonized.csv', index=False)\\nprint(f\\\"Saved to /root/ckd_lab_data_harmonized.csv\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Final shape: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\nVerifying output...\\\")\\ndf_verify = pd.read_csv('/root/ckd_lab_data_harmonized.csv')\\nprint(f\\\"Sample rows:\\\")\\nprint(df_verify[['patient_id', 'Serum_Creatinine', 'BUN', 'Hemoglobin', 'Magnesium', 'Serum_Calcium']].head(20))\\n\\nEOFHYBRID\\n\",\n      \"duration\": 0.5\n    },\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"python3 /tmp/harmonize_hybrid.py\\n\",\n      \"duration\": 3.0\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"
